page.title: 03Nap Wood,East Sussex
page.content: Nap Wood is a nature conservation area.It is some 114 acres in area. The highest point is 550 feet.Nap Wood is oak woodland. There are many other trees including beech,ash,yew,scots pine and near the streams the alders thrive. Nap Wood is really a beautiful spot, with carpets of bluebells in spring,and the wild life is interesting to watch.If you go through the wood you will spot bird boxes on trees which are regularly used in spring.You can sometimes see great spotted woodpeckers.If you look on the ground you may see signs of badgers, rabbits,foxes and squirrels.There are many badger's sets and foxes earths in the wood. The wood is left to nature for all to enjoy.
